g.text: custom : custom shell script, just passing variables
env : execute env on each pod and put to pod.env file
env-ac : execute env on each pod and put to pod.env file, auto close
env-at : execute env on each pod and put to pod.env file, auto attach
env-nginx-simple : execute env on each pod and put to pod.env file
env-nginx-simple-t : execute env on each pod and put to pod.env file, terminate tmux
exec-it-sh : execute sh on each pod in interactive mode and attach to tmux
kctl-exec-it-bash : execute bash on each pod in interactive mode and attach to tmux
logs1 : execute kubectl logs on each pod/container, pass it to local file then tail all files to console
logs2 : execute kubectl logs on each pod/container, pass it to local file then tail all files to console
ping-KubeSvcHost : install ping util and ping KUBERNETES_SERVICE_HOST env variable ip
procTcp : get /proc/net/tcp on each then convert it to netstat format
ps-tcpdump : check each pod if there is tcpdump process left running, attaches tmux
remote-exec : example of attaching to remote host with different prompt
strace-php : install strace and start strace on all php processes
tcpdump-all : tcpdump on any interface all traffic for 300 seconds or 100k packets
